==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tumbleweed
<hw>Tum"ble*weed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Any plant which habitually breaks away from its roots in the
autumn, and is driven by the wind, as a light, rolling mass, over the
fields and prairies; such as witch grass, wild indigo, <spn>Amarantus
albus</spn>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tumbling</ent>⟦br⟧
